    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just told me i need to deal with an escrow account for the house closing and im kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do we even need it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in simple terms, is like a temporary holding place for money and documents during a real estate transaction. Think of it as a neutral, trusted third party—the escrow company—holding the buyer's deposit and the seller's funds until all the conditions of the sale are met. It's crucial because it ensures both parties fulfill their obligations, preventing one side from getting the other's money and then backing out at the last minute. This process keeps the entire closing smooth, fair, and secure.",
